## Common Mistakes

- Presenting current web facts from memory instead of searching first.
- Assuming `{{SERVER_NAME}}` exists without checking inventory or its tool surface.
- Asking the user to troubleshoot the local install before confirming `{{SERVER_NAME}}` is absent from the MCP inventory.
- Hiding fallback usage instead of disclosing why it was needed and which sources backed the answer.
- Re-expanding the skill into duplicate sequence/reference sections or HTML tables instead of keeping one clear workflow.
